Avec cette option, le MENU suivant s'affiche
1; Print the values of a TMS (Tableau Memoire Secondaire)
2; INPUT the values of a TMS
3; Print a TMS variable value
4; IMPOSE the VALUE of a variable of a TMS
5; CHANGE a NAME in a Lexicon

An ARRAY in SECOND MEMORY STORAGE (TMS) is a set of informations
stored in direct access file on disk, which may be saved at any time
and recovers by its NAME defined by
- ~> the beginning (name of the tree of names)
- point or ligne or surface or volume or objet or transfo or ...
- the character  >  as separator.

Examples : 
~>ligne>l1>nsef; give the FE list of the line named L1
(excepted for a name file, upper or lower case letters are equals)
~> is the root of the data base.

~>surface>sphere>xyzsommet; give the FE list of 
coordinates of vertices of the FE of the surface named sphere.

