When the NAME has  >>  it is necessar to add between these 2 successive >
the name of the PLSVO
For example : 
To have the surface RECTANGLE definition, the name from
~>SURFACE>>DEFINITION is: ~>surface>rectangle>definition;

If the NAME begins with ~>>, it is necessary to preceed the name by a prefix
point or ligne or surface or volume or objet or transfo or ...
For example : ~>>>CONDUCTIVITE permits ~>volume>motor>conductivite;

If the NAME has lost some suffixes, the name represents a directory
which contains names of TMS which may be displayed
For example : point; gives the actual list of points.

~>ligne>axis; displays the TMS array list of the line names axis

To obtain the array list of the root of the tree, type ~>;

A LEXICON is  a TMS NAME without its suffix.
Example : ~>point;  or ~>point>p1;  or ~>surface>rectangle;

The NAME of a VARIABLE of a TMS is formed from
- the TMS array NAME
- following by (
- following by the identificator of the variable
- following by )
- ended by ;
Example :  ~>point>p1>xyzsommet(nbsom);  

If the variable is one of an array, the name of its identificator
is followed of
- (
- the value>0 of the first index
- ,  following the value of the second indice ...
- )
Example: ~>surface>octogon>nsef(nusoef(2,5));
dispay the number 2 of the FE 5 of the mesh of the surface
named octogon.


1; Print the values of a TMS (Tableau Memoire Secondaire)
The generation rules of a TMS NAME have been done previously
Example :
 1;
 ~>ligne>axis>xyzsommet; 
 {The coordinates of vertices of the line named axis}

2; INPUT the values of a TMS
The generation rules of a TMS NAME have been done previously
(cf the file $MEFISTO/td/d and the grammar dans $MEFISTO/td/d/grammaire)
Example :  2;   ~>ligne>axis>xyzsommet; 
 {The coordinates of vertices of line named axis}
 3;  {number of vertices}
 0;  {number of tangents}
 3;  {number of coordinates}
 0; 0;   0;    { 3 coordinates of vertex 1 }
 0; 0.5; 0;    { 3 coordinates of vertex 2 }
 0; 0;   1;    { 3 coordinates of vertex 3 }

3; Print a TMS variable value
The generation rules of a TMS VARIABLE NAME have been done previously
Example :
 3;
 ~>ligne>axis>xyzsommet(nbsom); 
 {The vertex number of the line named axis}

4; {IMPOSE the VALUE of a variable of a TMS}
The generation rules of a TMS VARIABLE NAME have been done previously
Examples :
 4;
 ~>ligne>axe>xyzsommet(nbsom);   {The NAME of the VARIABLE}
 5;      {vertices on the line named axis}

 4;
 ~>surface>s>xyzsommet(xyzsom(varut)(3))
 0; { the new value of z of vertex varut  the integer value of 
      the user's variable on the surface s }

ATTENTION: Every MODIFICATION is under the User's responsability.
If nbsom is greater than its old value, any call to this TMS => ERROR
Use this option only for local debugging!

5; CHANGE a NAME in a Lexicon
The generation rules of a LEXICON NAME have been done previously
Example :
 5;
 point;   {Changement of a POINT NAME}
 p1;      {Old NAME of the point}
 p2;      {New NAME of the point}
